To drive increase in the revenue base of the Nation, the Revenue Mobilization Allocation and Fiscal Commission (RMAFC) has engaged with the Department of Petroleum Resource (DPR) in Abuja. A statement by Christian Nwachukwu, the Head Public Relations, RMAFC quoted the chairman of the RMAFC Engineer Elias Mbam to have said that the DPR plays a major role in the revenue generation of the nation. He expressed concerns on the challenges in the oil sector of the economy such as oil theft which leads to reduction in oil revenue and the need to develop the gas sector. In his presentation, the acting director of DPR, Ahmad Rufai Shakur stated that although DPR collects oil and gas royalty the revenue is domiciled in the CBN. RMFAC backs subsidy removal RMAFC lauds Nigeriaâ€™s $15b cash for oil deal with India Revenue loss: Forum demands proper metering of oil, gas sector Kindly take one minute (1) of your time to fill out this short question. This questionnaire is designed to sample readers' opinions regarding what the feel about Daily Trust newspaper advertisement; it is not intended to used for any purpose other than to improve the quality of our newspapers. Any information provided will therefore be treated as confidential.